      "role": "user",
      "content": "makes sense. i'll try to get some soil test kits this weekend. i was also wondering about the roots—should i be digging around the base to check them for anything specific, like rot or pests, or is that gonna do more harm than good?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's generally best to avoid aggressive digging around the base unless you notice clear signs of severe distress. If you suspect rot or pests, gently excavating a small area near the root flare can provide clues. Look for soft, mushy roots (indicating rot) or tiny insects/webs. If the soil is heavily compacted or the base is totally surrounded by mulch, check those areas first instead of digging deeply.",
      "source": "target",
