      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, it is very common for root problems to develop underground before showing visible external symptoms. Root rot, fungal infections, or root-feeding pests can gradually damage the plant's ability to absorb water and nutrients, leading to yellowing leaves. Because the damage is internal, the foliage is often the very last thing to show signs of trouble. A basic soil inspection or professional consultation can often reveal these hidden issues.",
